### Task 3.5: Wire new checks into the Reasoner's `run` method


```rust
CheckType::MisplacedDoc => {
    if let Some(ref rules) = self.docs_rules {
        findings.extend(check_misplaced_doc(&entries, rules));
    }
},
CheckType::CoverageGap => {
    findings.extend(check_coverage_gap(&entries));
},
CheckType::TemporalContradiction => {
    let threshold = 0.85; // same as merge similarity_threshold
    findings.extend(check_temporal_contradiction(&entries, threshold));
},
```

`MisplacedDoc` is a no-op if `docs_rules` is `None` (graceful degradation for non-workspace configs). `CoverageGap` is deterministic (no LLM needed). `TemporalContradiction` uses embeddings from stored entries (no live inference needed — entries already have embeddings).

